      "writtenOn": "2020-04-30T11:49:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think you want something like:\n\nvar g errgroup.Group\n_ \u003d util.ChunkIter(len(gms), batchSize, func(start, end int) error {\n  g.Go(func() error {\n    ...\n  })\n  return nil\n})\nif err :\u003d g.Wait(); err !\u003d nil {\n  td.Fatal(ctx, err)\n}\n\nWe do have util.ChunkIterParallel, but it\u0027ll try to stop after the first error, which I don\u0027t think is what you want here: https://skia.googlesource.com/buildbot/+/master/go/util/util.go#446\n\nIt might also be nice to wrap this up in a parent step, but that comes down to personal preference of what you want to see on the UI.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 57,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 62,
        "endChar": 22
      },
      "revId": "58806f2cf832c5a31a0d8eb515a41c1bebcb46fa",
