        "id": 5045
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-04-30T12:27:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Is that errgroup.Group this https://godoc.org/golang.org/x/sync/errgroup ?\n\nI\u0027m reading there\n\n   func (g *Group) Go(f func() error)\n   Go calls the given function in a new goroutine.\n\n   The first call to return a non-nil error cancels the group; its error will be returned by Wait.\n\nThat\u0027s not what I want, right?  What does it mean to cancel the group?  That also doesn\u0027t let me count the failures right?  It\u0027d just be Fatal()ing with an arbitrary one of the subprocess failures?\n\nCan you explain what you mean about parent steps?",
      "parentUuid": "0ab5fb90_bdff9b60",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 57,
        "startChar": 0,
